      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEEP LOVE NZ (3) has been freshened since a solid fourth in the Gold Coronet at Bathurst and that looks a strong form race as it was taken out by a G1 winner and the runner-up went on to win the NSW Oaks. Scored back-to-back wins before that series. Kept up to the mark with two trials and looks well placed aided by a good draw. AETOS DYNAMIS (2) produced a good effort to finish second two starts ago at Shepparton then worked hard when caught wide last start. Draws well and has won here before. BULLAPARK BENO (8) draws for a trail and can feature again after finishing third at Bendigo last time out. DELS DESTINY NZ (7) eases back in grade on the last attempt and had recorded a series of wins or placings prior.",
